posts.post_content: Looking for sharp examples, low population cards even better....thanks
Have a very well-centered Rudolph PSA 7--I think it's top graded--and with a very subtle and attractive wet transfer in the red, to boot...

Hi Greg,
Would you mind posting or emailing a scan of this T206 Rudolph PSA 7?  Want to see this wet transfer and also the corners... big thx,
Rick.

[quote name="GregMitch34" post=1067631]Have a very well-centered Rudolph PSA 7--I think it's top graded--and with a very subtle and attractive wet transfer in the red, to boot...[/QUOTE]

Hello, here are the front and back of the Rudolph, not the best scans but okay.  I have TRIED to show the wet transfer but as I said it is quite subtle (nicely so), can only see when tilt card in the light--then you see clearly the imprint of the slanted Piedmont filling the dark red portion in upper left of card.  These scans make it look fuzzy but it is not at all.
